						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> (proper right side) of the Paṭṭābhirāmasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>ACHYUTADĒVARĀYA.</p>						

						<p>1534 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1456, Jaya, Śrāvaṇa, śu. 1. corresponding to July 12, Sunday, 1534, A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. Seems to register the gift of land in Vāvilipāṭi village situated in the division Kandanavrōlu to the god Raghunāthadēva by <hi rend="italic">mahānāyamkāchāryya</hi> Kam[bham] Timmanāyyani Venkaṭādri Nāyaka. The Kandanavrōlu is said to have given as <hi rend="italic">nāyamkara</hi> to the donor by the king.</p>						

						</summary>
